    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-11-21T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-11-21T17:00:00-05:00" n="523"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d523">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115/20489a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at London</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hollis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-11-21T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 21, 1919—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s May 29, 1917, 5 p.m.<note n="32" xml:id="d523fn32">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_601">p. 601</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Please cable list of all pending cases whether in Prize Court or on appeal
                    resulting from seizure of vessels or cargoes in which American concerns are
                    interested. Report in detail by mail concerning means to effect prompt
                    settlement of these cases to prevent further irritation resulting from them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
